ing: 1 (2 ounce) package dried beef, finely chopped
1 (2.25 ounce) can sliced black olives, drained
des: "I take this recipe to family and friend get togethers and it's always a hit. It's quick to put together. Serve it with an assortment of crackers, or try it with green olives."
ins: Place the cream cheese, sour cream, milk, horseradish, onion, and dill in a bowl, and stir until well blended. Gently fold in the beef and black olives. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours, or overnight to blend flavors before serving.
